RDG PRINCIPLE:
A tensor is an operator with N relational translation slots.
Rank = number of independent relational directions.
Each index = one translation operator T(·) acting in a distinct RDG axis.
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

SCALAR (rank 0)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG form:   S
Meaning:    No translation slots; no relational displacement.
ASCII:      S
RDG role:   Pure structural value.

VECTOR (rank 1)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG form:   v_i  =  T_i • v
Meaning:    One relational direction.
ASCII:      [v1 v2 v3 ...]
RDG role:   Single-axis relational displacement.

MATRIX (rank 2)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG form:   M_ij  =  T_i T_j • M
Meaning:    Two independent relational directions.
ASCII:      m11 m12 m13 ...
            m21 m22 m23 ...
RDG role:   Bi-directional relational grid.

3‑TENSOR (rank 3)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG form:   A_ijk  =  T_i T_j T_k • A
Meaning:    Three relational directions; relational cube.
ASCII:      A(:,:,1), A(:,:,2), ...
RDG role:   Tri-directional relational operator.

4‑TENSOR (rank 4)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RDG form:   B_ijkl  =  T_i T_j T_k T_l • B
Meaning:    Four relational directions; hypercube of relational operators.
ASCII:      B(:,:,:,1), B(:,:,:,2), ...
RDG role:   Extended relational operator with auxiliary axis.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GENERAL RULE (RDG)
Rank = number of relational translation operators T(·).
Dimension = size of each operator’s domain.
Rank ≠ dimension.
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

RDG OPERATOR INTERPRETATION
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Index slot i  →  relational displacement operator T_i
Tensor rank N →  N-fold relational composition T_i1 T_i2 ... T_iN
Tensor entry  →  evaluation of the composed operator on a base state

Example:
A_ijk = T_i T_j T_k • A
means: apply relational displacement i, then j, then k.

